						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Nāgēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10 = 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Built in at the right end. Seems to record the donation of sheep by Kōyil Mayilai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Madhurāntaka Mūvēndavēḷāṉ and also probably by Mayilai Kōyil <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Neriyaṉ Mūvēndavēḷāṉ for contributing ghee. Other details are lost. The inscription also mentions a charity house <hi rend="italic">(aṟachchālai)</hi> in the temple.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">Kuḍandaik kalveṭṭukkaḷ.</hi> Vol. I No. 15/1979. </p>						

						</summary>
